  abstract={By combining the strengths of the Santa Cruz semi-analytic model and the IllustrisTNG100 simulation, we developed the TNG SAM, a fast model calibrated to reproduce TNG’s gas and metal flows in stellar-feedback–dominated galaxies. We show that physically motivated updates to cooling, star formation, recycling, outflows, and gas re-accretion allow the SAM to recover TNG’s baryon cycle and global galaxy properties to within $\sim$30\% out to $z=6$. This work demonstrates that well-calibrated SAMs can capture much of the complex physics of hydrodynamical simulations while enabling efficient parameter studies across cosmological volumes.}
